#. type: Content of: <section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:212
msgid "<emphasis>Script: Generating a new certificate.</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Skript: Neues Zertifikat erstellen.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:219
msgid ""
"Now that these operations have been performed, the S/MIME setup must be "
"completed in OTRS."
msgstr ""
"Nach der Durchführung dieser Schritte ist es notwendig die Einrichtung von S/"
"MIME in OTRS abzuschließen."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:223
msgid ""
"This part of the setup is carried out in the Admin page, choosing the link "
"<link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">\"SMIME\"</link>. In case the general S/"
"MIME support in OTRS has not yet been enabled, the mask points this out to "
"the administrator and provides an appropriate link for enabling it."
msgstr ""
"Die OTRS-seitige Einrichtung erfolgt aus dem Admin-Bereich, Block System "
"über den Punkt <link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">SMIME</link>. Falls die "
"generelle S/MIME-Unterstützung in OTRS noch nicht aktiviert wurde, weist die "
"Maske den OTRS-Administrator beim Aufruf darauf hin und bietet einen "
"bequemen Link zur Einrichtung."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:227
msgid ""
"With the SysConfig group <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Crypt::"
"SMIME\">\"Crypt::SMIME\"</link>, you can also enable and configure the "
"general S/MIME support."
msgstr ""
"Über die SysConfig-Gruppe <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Crypt::"
"SMIME\">\"Crypt::SMIME\"</link>, kann die generelle S/MIME-Unterstützung "
"eingeschaltet und konfiguriert werden. "

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:231
msgid ""
"Here you can activate S/MIME support, and define the paths for the OpenSSL "
"command and the directory for the certificates. The key file created above "
"must be stored in the directory indicated here. Otherwise OpenSSL cannot use "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Hier können sie S/MIME-Unterstützung aktivieren, und die Pfade zum OpenSSL-"
"Kommando und zu den Zertifikaten angeben. Die vorhin erzeugte Schlüsseldatei "
"muss in diesem Verzeichnis gespeichert werden, sonst kann OpenSSL sie nicht "
"verwenden."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:235
msgid ""
"The next step is performed in the <link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">S/MIME "
"configuration on the OTRS Admin page</link>. Here, you can import the "
"private key(s) of the OTRS system and the public keys of other communication "
"partners. Enter the public key that has been created in the beginning of "
"this section and added to OTRS."
msgstr ""
"Im nächsten Schritt geht es (zurück) zur <link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">S/"
"MIME-Konfiguration</link> im Administrationsbereich. Dort können nun sowohl "
"der private Schlüssel(Key) bzw. die privaten Schlüssel des OTRS-Systems, als "
"auch die öffentlichen Schlüssel anderer Kommunikationspartner ins System "
"importiert werden. Tragen Sie hier den öffentlichen Schlüssel ein, der zu "
"Beginn dieses Abschnitts erzeugt und dann in OTRS hinzugefügt wurde."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:239
msgid ""
"Obviously, all public S/MIME keys of communication partners can be imported "
"using the <link linkend=\"adminarea-customers\">customer administration "
"tool</link> as well."
msgstr ""
"Selbstverständlich können aber auch alle öffentlichen S/MIME-Schlüssel der "
"Kommunikationspartner über das <link linkend=\"adminarea-customers\">Modul "
"zur Kundenverwaltung</link> beim Anlegen/Bearbeiten des jeweiligen Kunden in "
"das System importiert werden."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:6
msgid "Time Related Functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:9
msgid "Setting up business hours, holidays and time zones"
msgstr "Arbeitszeiten, Feiertage und Zeitzonen für das System festlegen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:12
msgid ""
"Some functions in OTRS, like escalations and <link linkend=\"unlock-tickets"
"\">automatic unlocking of tickets</link>, depend on a proper configuration "
"of business hours, time zones and holidays. You can define these via the "
"<link linkend=\"sysconfig\">SysConfig interface</link>, in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time\">Framework &gt; Core::Time</link>.  "
"You can also specify different sets of business hours, holidays and time "
"zones as separate 'Calendars' in <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:"
"Core::Time::Calendar1\">Framework &gt; Core::Time::Calendar1</link> through "
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time::Calendar9\">Framework "
"&gt; Core::Time::Calendar9</link>. Calendars can be defined by <link linkend="
"\"adminarea-queue\">queue settings</link>, or on SLA levels. This means "
"that, for example, you can specify a calendar with 5 x 8 business hours for "
"your 'standard' SLA, but create a separate calendar with 7 x 24 support for "
"your 'gold' SLA; as well as set a calendar for your 'Support-USA' queue with "
"a different time window than your 'Support-Japan' queue. OTRS can handle up "
"to 99 different calendars."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:17
msgid "Business Hours"
msgstr "Arbeitszeiten"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:20
msgid ""
"Set up the working hours for your system in SysConfig <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time:TimeWorkingHours\">Framework &gt; "
"Core::Time::TimeWorkingHours</link>, or for your specific calendar in the "
"calendar's configuration. OTRS can handle a granularity of one hour. "
"Checking the marks in the boxes 8, 9, 10 ... 17 corresponds with business "
"hours of 8 AM - 6 PM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:24
msgid ""
"Only during business hours can tickets escalate, notifications for escalated "
"and pending tickets be sent, and tickets be unlocked."
msgstr ""
"Nur während dieser Stunden können Tickets eskalieren, Benachrichtigungen zu "
"Erinnerungs-Tickets versendet oder Tickets automatisch freigegeben werden. "
"Weiterhin werden auch nur diese Stunden in die Berechnung der "
"Eskalationszeit und der Zeit für die automatische Freigabe mit einbezogen."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:30
msgid "Fixed Date Holidays"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:33
msgid ""
"Holidays that are on a fixed date every year, such as New Year's Day or the "
"Fourth of July, can be specified in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time:TimeVacationDays\">TimeVacationDays</"
"link>, or in the corresponding section for the calendars 1-9."
msgstr ""
"Feiertage deren Datum jedes Jahr gleich ist, wie Neujahr oder der vierte "
"Juli, können in <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time:"
"TimeVacationDays\">TimeVacationDays </link> oder im entsprechenden Abschnitt "
"in den Kalendern 1-9 konfiguriert werden."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:37
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate nor get unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDays."
msgstr ""
"Während der hier festgelegten Tage werden keine zeitabhängigen Aktionen oder "
"Berechnungen auf Tickets im system ausgeführt."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:42
msgid ""
"By default, OTRS ships with the <emphasis>German</emphasis> holidays "
"installed."
msgstr ""
"In OTRS sind die <emphasis>deutschen</emphasis> Feiertage voreingestellt."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:49
msgid "Floating Holidays"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:52
msgid ""
"Holidays such as Easter that do not have a yearly fixed date but instead "
"vary each year, can be specified in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time:TimeVacationDaysOneTime"
"\">TimeVacationDaysOneTime</link>."
msgstr ""
"Feiertage, wie Ostern, für die sich jährlich das Datum ändert, können in "
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::Time:TimeVacationDaysOneTime"
"\"> TimeVacationDaysOneTime </link> konfiguriert werden."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:56
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate and will not be unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDaysOneTime."
msgstr ""
"Während der hier festgelegten Tage werden keine zeitabhängigen Aktionen oder "
"Berechnungen auf Tickets im system ausgeführt."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:61
msgid ""
"OTRS does not ship with any One-Time holidays pre-installed. This means that "
"you need to add holidays, such as Easter or Thanksgiving, to the system when "
"configuring OTRS."
msgstr ""
"OTRS hat für diese Feiertage keine Voreinstellung. Sie müssen diese, wie z. "
"B. Ostern, dem System also selbst bekannt machen."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:70
msgid "Automated Unlocking"
msgstr "Automatische Ticket-\"Freigabe\" (unlock)"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:73
msgid ""
"Locked tickets can be automatically unlocked by the system. This feature "
"might be useful if, for example, an agent has locked tickets that need to be "
"processed, but he can't work on them for some reason, say because he is out "
"of the office on an emergency. The automated unlock feature unlocks tickets "
"after a given time to ensure that no locked tickets will be forgotten, "
"thereby allowing other agents to process them."
msgstr ""
"Gesperrte Tickets können automatisch vom System freigegeben werden. Diese "
"Funktion kann z. B. dann nützlich sein, wenn sich ein Agent im Urlaub "
"befindet und noch Tickets gesperrt hat, die bearbeitet werden sollen / "
"müssen. Dieses Feature entsperrt Tickets nach einer bestimmten Zeit, um "
"sicherzustellen, dass gesperrte Tickets nicht vergessen werden und andere "
"Agenten darauf zugreifen können."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:77
msgid ""
"The amount of time before a ticket is unlocked can be specified in the <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-queue\">queue settings</link> for every queue. The "
"command <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Ticket::Unlock</filename>, "
"which is executed periodically as a cron job, performs the automated "
"unlocking of tickets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:81
msgid ""
"Notifications on unlocked tickets are sent out only to those agents that "
"have the queue with the unlocked tickets set in \"My queues\", and that have "
"activated the notification on unlocked tickets in their personal <link "
"linkend=\"user-preferences\">preferences</link>."
msgstr ""
"Benachrichtigungen für entsperrte Tickets werden nur zu den Benutzern "
"versendet, die die jeweilige Queue in \"Meine Queues\" eingetragen und die "
"Benachrichtigung für entsperrte Tickets in ihren <link linkend=\"user-"
"preferences\"> persönlichen Einstellungen </link> aktiviert haben."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:85
msgid "Tickets will be unlocked if all of the following conditions are met:"
msgstr "Tickets werden entsperrt wenn folgende Bedingungen zutreffen:"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:91
msgid ""
"There is an <emphasis>unlock timeout</emphasis> defined for the queue the "
"ticket is in."
msgstr ""
"In der Queue des Tickets ist ein <emphasis>Freigabe-Zeitintervall</emphasis> "
"definiert."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:96
msgid "The ticket is set to <emphasis>locked</emphasis>."
msgstr "Das Ticket ist <emphasis>gesperrt</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:101
msgid "The ticket state is <emphasis>open</emphasis>."
msgstr "Der Status des Tickets is <emphasis>offen\"</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:107
msgid ""
"The unlock timer will be reset if an agent adds a new external article to "
"the ticket. It can be of any of the following types: <emphasis>email-"
"external</emphasis>, <emphasis>phone</emphasis>, <emphasis>fax</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>sms</emphasis>, or <emphasis>note-external</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Die Freigabezeit wird zurückgesetzt, wenn ein Agent einen neuen externen "
"Artikel zum Ticket hinzufügt. Das kann einer der folgenden Artikeltypen "
"sein: <emphasis>email-external</emphasis>, <emphasis>phone</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>fax</emphasis>, <emphasis>sms</emphasis>, or <emphasis>note-"
"external</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:111
msgid ""
"Also, if the last article in the ticket is created by an agent, and a "
"customer adds another one, either via web or email response, the unlock "
"timer will be reset."
msgstr ""
"Die Freigabezeit wird auch zurückgesetzt, wenn der letzte Artikel von einem "
"Agent stammt und dann der Kunde einen hinzufügt, per E-Mail oder "
"Weboberfläche."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/time.xml:115
msgid ""
"The last event that will reset the unlock timer is when the ticket is "
"assigned to another agent."
msgstr ""
"Zuletzt wird die Freigabezeit auch dann zurückgesetzt, wenn das Ticket einem "
"anderen Agenten zugewiesen wird."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:4
msgid "Customizing the PDF Output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:7
msgid "This section handles the configurable options for PDF output in OTRS."
msgstr ""
"Dieser Abschnitt behandelt die Einstellungen für die PDF-Druckausgabe von "
"OTRS."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:11
msgid ""
"If you use the Print action from anywhere within the OTRS interface, it will "
"generate a formatted PDF file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:14
msgid ""
"You can adjust the look of the files generated by OTRS by creating your own "
"logo and adding it to <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::PDF:"
"PDF::LogoFile\">PDF::LogoFile</link>. You can use <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::PDF:PDF::PageSize\">PDF::PageSize</link> "
"to define the standard page size of the generated PDF file (DIN-A4 or "
"Letter), and also <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Framework:Core::PDF:PDF::"
"MaxPages\">PDF::MaxPage</link> to specify the maximum number of pages for a "
"PDF file, which is useful if a user generates a huge output file by mistake."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:5
msgid "Generic Interface"
msgstr "Generic Interface"

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:7
msgid ""
"The OTRS Generic Interface consists of a multiple layer framework that lets "
"OTRS communicate with other systems via a web service. This communication "
"could be bi-directional:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:13
msgid ""
"<emphasis>OTRS as Provider: </emphasis> OTRS acts as a server listening to "
"requests from the External System, processing the information, performing "
"the requested action, and answering the request."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:20
msgid ""
"<emphasis>OTRS as Requester: </emphasis> OTRS acts as a client collecting "
"information, sending the request to the Remote System, and waiting for the "
"response."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:32
msgid ""
"A Web Service is a communication method between two systems, in our case "
"OTRS and a Remote System."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:36
msgid ""
"The heart of the Web Service is its configuration, where it is defined what "
"actions the web service can perform internally (Operation), what actions the "
"OTRS request can perform Remote System (Invokers), how data is converted "
"from one system to the other (Mapping), and over which protocol the "
"communication will take place (Transport)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:42
msgid ""
"The Generic Interface is the framework that makes it possible to create Web "
"Services for OTRS in a predefined way, using already made building blocks "
"that are independent from each other and interchangeable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:6
msgid "Ticket Priorities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:9
msgid ""
"OTRS comes with five default priority levels that can be modified via the "
"\"Priorities\" link on the Admin page. When creating a customized list of "
"priorities, please keep in mind that they are sorted alphabetically in the "
"priority selection box in the user interface. Also, OTRS orders tickets by "
"internal database IDs in the QueueView."
msgstr ""
"OTRS enthält 5 vordefinierte Ticketprioritäten, die mit dem \"Prioritäten\"-"
"Modul im Administrationsbereich verwaltet werden können. Wenn Sie eine "
"angepasste Prioritätenliste erstellen, bedenken Sie bitte, dass diese in der "
"Prioritätsauswahl-Liste alphabetisch sortiert dargestellt werden. In der "
"Queue-Ansicht ordnet OTRS die Prioritäten nach internen Datenbank-IDs."

#. type: Content of: <section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:14
msgid ""
"As with other OTRS entities, priorities may not be deleted, only deactivated "
"by setting the Valid option to <emphasis>invalid</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>invalid-temporarily</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"In OTRS können Prioritäten deaktiviert, aber nicht gelöscht werden. Wenn Sie "
"eine Priorität deaktivieren wollen, setzen Sie den Wert für \"Gültig\" auf "
"\"ungültig\" oder \"ungültig-temporär\"."

#. type: Content of: <section><important><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:20
msgid ""
"If a new priority was added or if an existing one was changed, you might "
"also want to modify some values in SysConfig:"
msgstr ""
"Wenn eine Priorität hinzugefügt oder geändert wurde, müssen Sie ggf. einige "
"Werte in der SysConfig anpassen:"

#. type: Content of: <section><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:24
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Core::PostMaster:"
"PostmasterDefaultPriority\"> Ticket:Core::Postmaster::"
"PostmasterDefaultPriority</link> - defines the default priority for all "
"incoming emails."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Core::PostMaster:"
"PostmasterDefaultPriority\"> Ticket:Core::Postmaster::"
"PostmasterDefaultPriority</link> - definiert die Standard-Priorität für alle "
"eingehenden E-Mails."

#. type: Content of: <section><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:27
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Agent::Ticket::ViewPhoneNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::AgentTicketPhone_Priority\"> Ticket:Frontend::Agent:"
"Ticket::ViewPhoneNew:Priority</link> - defines the default priority in the "
"New Phone Ticket screen for agents."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Agent::Ticket::ViewPhoneNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::AgentTicketPhone_Priority\"> Ticket:Frontend::Agent:"
"Ticket::ViewPhoneNew:Priority</link> - definiert die Standard-Priorität in "
"der Oberfläche 'Neues Telefonticket' für Agenten."

#. type: Content of: <section><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:30
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Agent::Ticket::ViewEmailNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::AgentTicketEmail_Priority\"> Ticket:Frontend::Agent:"
"Ticket::ViewEmailNew:Priority</link> - defines the default priority in the "
"New Email Ticket screen for agents."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Agent::Ticket::ViewEmailNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::AgentTicketEmail_Priority\"> Ticket:Frontend::Agent:"
"Ticket::ViewEmailNew:Priority</link> - definiert die Standard-Priorität in "
"der Oberfläche 'Neues E-Mailticket' für Agenten."

#. type: Content of: <section><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:33
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Customer::Ticket::ViewNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::CustomerTicketMessage_PriorityDefault\"> Ticket:Frontend::"
"Customer:Ticket::ViewNew:PriorityDefault</link> - defines the default "
"priority in the New Ticket screen in the Customer frontend."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Ticket:Frontend::Customer::Ticket::ViewNew:"
"Ticket::Frontend::CustomerTicketMessage_PriorityDefault\"> Ticket:Frontend::"
"Customer:Ticket::ViewNew:PriorityDefault</link> - definiert die Standard-"
"Priorität in der Oberfläche 'Neues Ticket' im Kunden-Interface."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:6
msgid "Ticket States"
msgstr "Ticket Status"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:9
msgid "Predefined states"
msgstr "Vordefinierte Ticket-Status"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:12
msgid ""
"OTRS allows you to change predefined ticket states and their types, or even "
"add new ones. Two attributes are important for a state: the state name and "
"the state type."
msgstr ""
"OTRS erlaubt es Ihnen, die Ticket-Status zu verändern oder neue Status "
"hinzuzufügen. Hierbei gibt es zwei wichtige Optionen: den Namen des Status "
"und Typ des Status."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:16
msgid ""
"The default states of OTRS are: 'closed successful', 'closed unsuccessful', "
"'merged', 'new', 'open', 'pending auto close+', 'pending auto close-', "
"'pending reminder' and 'removed'."
msgstr ""
"Die standardmäßig voreingestellten Status lauten: 'neu', 'offen', "
"'erfolgreich geschlossen', 'erfolglos geschlossen', 'merged', 'entfernt', "
"'warten auf erfolgreich schließen', 'warten auf erfolglos schließen' und "
"'warten zur Erinnerung'. "

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:20
msgid "New"
msgstr "Neu"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:22
msgid "Tickets are usually in this state when created from incoming e-mails."
msgstr ""
"Tickets sind normalerweise nur in diesem Status, wenn sie von eingehenden E-"
"Mails neu erzeugt werden."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:27
msgid "Open"
msgstr "Öffnen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:29
msgid "This is the default state for tickets assigned to queues and agents."
msgstr "Der Standardstatus für Tickets, die Queues und Agents zugeordnet sind."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:34
msgid "Pending reminder"
msgstr "Warten zur Erinnerung"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/states.xml:36
msgid ""
"After the pending time has expired, the ticket owner will receive a reminder "
"email concerning the ticket. If the ticket is not locked, the reminder will "
"be sent to all agents in the queue. Reminder tickets will only be sent out "
"during business hours, and are repeatedly sent every 24 hours until the "
"ticket state is changed by the agent. Time spent by the ticket in this "
"status will still add towards the escalation time calculation."
msgstr ""
"Nachdem die Wartezeit abgelaufen ist, erhält der Ticketbesitzer eine E-Mail "
"zu dem Ticket. Wenn es nicht gesperrt ist, wird die Erinnerung an alle "
"Agenten der Queue verschickt. Erinnerungs-Benachrichtigungen werden nur "
"innerhalb der Arbeitszeiten versendet, und werden alle 24 Stunden "
"wiederholt, bis der Status des Tickets vom Agenten verändert wird. Die Zeit, "
"die dieses Ticket in diesem Status verbringt, wird dennoch bei der "
